            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Use your Google Business Profile format as the canonical reference. GBP is Google's most trusted source, so matching that exact format everywhere — same business name, address formatting, phone format — signals a single unified entity.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long until consistency fixes impact rankings?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Local pack ranking improvements typically appear within 30 to 60 days of the corrections landing. Data aggregator corrections take 4 to 8 weeks to propagate downstream, so full consistency across every source can take 2 to 3 months to lock in.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does 'Main St' vs 'Main Street' actually matter?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Search algorithms compare NAP strings and treat variations as conflicting data. Standardizing on one form of every element — abbreviations, suffixes, punctuation — is the whole point of consistency.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Should I include suite numbers on citations?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes if the suite is on your Google Business Profile — the goal is match, not preference. Whatever GBP shows is the canonical form; every citation follows that exactly.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

